(a) a poundmaster of any pound in his District subject to the terms of the contract entered into between the District Secretary and such poundmaster: Provided that— (i) no person shall at the same time be poundmaster of more than one pound ; and (ii) no person shall be appointed or continue as poundmaster who is a licensed dealer in intoxicating liquor;
