Any poundmaster may destroy, subject to the exceptions hereinafter stated, any impounded animal suffering from a contagious disease, or likely to prove dangerous to human life, or destructive to other animals impounded: Provided that—
(i) the poundmaster shall completely and effectually isolate any diseased animal away from any road;
