Every person who delivers any animals to a poundmaster to be impounded shall be entitled to receive from such poundmaster mileage at the rate set forth in the First Schedule: Provided that—
(i) when the person so delivering the said animals is not himself the owner of the land trespassed upon, or the caretaker for the owner , then he shall produce a written memorandum signed by such owner or caretaker giving a description of the animals, and authorising the bearer to convey them to the pound , and every such memorandum shall be preserved by the poundmaster as a voucher;
when the person so delivering the said animals is not himself the owner of the land trespassed upon, or the caretaker for the owner , then he shall produce a written memorandum signed by such owner or caretaker giving a description of the animals, and authorising the bearer to convey them to the pound , and every such memorandum shall be preserved by the poundmaster as a voucher;
(ii) when more persons than one have been necessarily employed in conveying the said animals to the pound , mileage shall only be paid by the poundmaster to one of such persons; but the person impounding the animals may recover from the owner thereof, in any competent court, similar mileage in respect of every other such person so employed.
